p:
Our unit of analysis is a claim, defined as a ‘unit of action in the public sphere’ (
 Koopmans and Statham, 1999; 
 Ylä-Anttila and Luhtakallio, 2016). It can be, for instance, a statement made in an interview, an op-ed, or the publication of a study that is reported in the media. One newspaper article may, therefore, contain several claims or none at all. In total, we found 1196 claims that included evaluations, and these claims constitute our final sample.
